  "prompt": "What universities does Scivac Therapeutics recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "As of my last training cut-off in October 2023, there isn't specific public information readily available about the exact universities that Scivac Therapeutics recruits new grads from or the specific majors they target. However, companies in the biopharmaceutical industry, such as Scivac Therapeutics, typically recruit from universities that have strong programs in life sciences, biomedical engineering, chemistry, pharmacology, and related fields. They often look for candidates with degrees in areas such as:\n\n1. Biology\n2. Biotechnology\n3. Biochemistry\n4. Biomedical Engineering\n5. Chemistry\n6. Pharmacology\n7. Molecular Biology\n8. Chemical Engineering\n\nGraduate programs at major research universities, such as Harvard, MIT, Stanford, UC Berkeley, Johns Hopkins, and University of Pennsylvania, are often targeted by companies in the biopharma sector. Scivac Therapeutics would likely follow similar patterns in seeking top talent from these and similar institutions.\n\nFor specific details on recruiting practices and targeted majors, it would be best to contact Scivac Therapeutics directly or check their website and current job postings.",
